page.title: 01MILDENHALL FEN
page.content: Approximately 7 miles north of Mildonhall. Flat, Fen, Farmland. Approached by Cooks Drove, a rough third class road. Top soil in area of peat about one to three feet deep with subsoil of gravel and sand. Area used almost exclusively for growing roots and barley. Whole area drained artificially by open ditches into main open drains maintained by Mildenhall Drainage. Area approx. 3 to 5 feet above ordinance Datum Board. No dwellings in the area. Some fields are outlined with Populars or Pine Trees to provide wind breaks - (not nearly enough).
